	"entries": [
		"A wall of crackling lightning springs into existence at a point you choose within range. The wall appears in any orientation you choose, as a horizontal or vertical barrier or at an angle. It can be free floating or resting on a solid surface. You can make the wall up to 60 feet long and 20 feet high. The wall is always 1 inch thick. The area the wall occupies is lightly obscured.",
		"When the wall appears, each creature in its area makes a Dexterity saving throw. On a failure a creature takes {@damage 4d6} Lightning damage and becomes {@condition Stunned|XPHB} until the end of your next turn. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage only.",
		"One side of the wall, selected by you when you cast this spell, deals {@damage 4d6} Lightning damage to each creature that ends its turn within 10 feet of that side or inside the wall. A creature takes the same damage when it enters the wall for the first time on a turn or ends its turn there. The other side of the wall deals no damage."
	],
